getTransformator

public OWLTransformator getTransformator(boolean failIfUnspecified)
                                  throws ExecutionException
Description copied from interface: JavaVariable
Convenience method. It assumes that a OWL transformator is specified and that the string is a fully qualified Java class name. The class will be loaded, instantiated using the default no-args constructor, and returned.

Specified by:
getTransformator in interface JavaVariable
Parameters:
failIfUnspecified - Determines whether to throw ExecutionException if no transformator is specified for this Java variable, i.e., when the parameter is false and a transformator is not specified it is silently ignored.
Returns:
OWL transformator instance, or null if unspecified and failIfUnspecified is false.
Throws:
ExecutionException - If failIfUnspecified is true and no transformator is specified.
